</span><hr size=1> About the 50-59 warrior lacking the ability to aggro monsters of a higher level; my question to you is, what would a 50-59 warrior be doing that for? I know not everyone is 60, but most 60+ mobs are usually killed and tanked by guilds that have level 60 warriors (to my knowledge).<br>
<br>
Anyway, I will try to further this discussion later when I have more time. I have yet to see why shadow knight self only aggro spells are of such concern (since before the DC nerf they were able to do this anyways). And I really do not see why a spell that will help a warrior achieve a 20% taunt modifier would upset you.<br>
<br>
To Varaho:<br>
In one of these threads I pointed it out why knights tanking big stuff isnt effective. There are times when knights make superior tanks (such as fast killing situations) but those are few and far between. The reason you dont put a knight up to tank the other mobs is because they lack the hitpoints and damage mitigation skills of a warrior. I have played a warrior, and a shadowknight, and a couple of other classes at the high end raiding game. I assure you to have a warlord tank things *IS BETTER*. Nearly any class can pull aggro off of anyone, but why would they want to. How many raid mobs are there with significantly less than 100k hp? The ones I can think of are...<br>
<br>
VS - usually manaburned, best to have a riposte/parry tank<br>
Trak - who cares, tanks get trak touched hardly a MT fight<br>
Sev - He hits for minimal damage<br>
Gore - Best to have a knight tank (if they dont get feared) because of the slow.<br>
Talendor - Never killed him, gets burned a lot<br>
Ragefire - He doesnt exist<br>
VP - Been here a few times, didnt tank.<br>
Master Yael - I dont wanna tank DT mobs, not a MT fight<br>
Fear Golems - See yael.<br>
Naggy / Vox (for sub 53 crowd) - umm 60 people rusing a mob (at least on my server) hardly a MT fight.<br>
<br>
Most of that is about 2.5 year old content and to be honest a caster could tank some of those mobs. I am sure a shaman would hold aggro well.<br>
<br>
And on uber hp mobs I assure you that you need a warrior so you dont burn through cleric mana spam CHing a sub par tank for a 30 minute fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/26/02 10:44:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1137.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  And on uber hp mobs I assure you that you need a warrior so you dont burn through cleric mana spam CHing a sub par tank for a 30 minute fight. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The actual question is, can the mob do enough damage between CHs to kill the character out right?  If a mob does 5k damage in 4 seconds, you have a 4 second CH cycle, and the character tanking has 6k, the MT lives.<br>
<br>
If a mob does 7k in that same time period then you need a MT with 7.5k, right?<br>
<br>
Of course you can reduce your CH cycle to 2 seconds instead, and have a reasonable chance of keeping that MT standing.<br>
<br>
It all comes down to how much damage is getting through and how many HP the character has.  Frankly, with most mobs, anything over 6k HP is gravy.  There might be a few that really require more, but not many. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A> at: 8/26/02 10:47:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/26/02 10:51:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1137.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Well, I have to admit, I just don't see how they are going to work it so that a shield increases a Warrior's agro similar to his wielding a procing off hand weapon without giving the Knights the exact same utility. And thereby making their agro generating the equal of a Warrior's before they cast a single spell. Sounds like a formula to increase Knight agro generation through the roof, to me. We'll see.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
