<br>
The other requirement for MT is holding aggro.  Since Knights can maintain aggro far better than any warrior wielding any weapon in the game they are a better choice for MT because the raid as a whole can increase it's DPS.  This makes the mob die faster and the MT as well as the rest of the raid take less damage overall.  The actually CHs on the MT might be slightly less mana efficient due to the slight HP advantage of a warrior in the same gear, but the efficiency of the raid as a whole is much higher with a Knight MTing than with a warrior MTing.<br>
<br>
Because of this it would be bettter to replace all warriors with rogues or monks for damage output and let the knights do all the tanking.<br>
<br>
For warriors to be viable as the most efficient choice for MT (we're not asking to be the only ones capable of it, just the most efficient), there are 2 things you can do.  You can either make warriors way ahead of any other class in damage mitigation and leave aggro management the way it is or you can leave mitigation the way it is and give warriors the same ability to get aggro at will that Knights have.  In my mind the second option would be preferable. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85547>Khumak</a><br>
60 Warrior<br>
Mith Marr<br>
